OL,3,CFather handed hospital order after
OL,4,Ckilling his newborn son
OL,6,FJudge Mr Justice Choudhury, who
OL,7,Fordered for Mohammed to be detained,
OL,8,Fsaid he had been "by all accounts a
OL,9,Fkind and loving man" who had doted on
OL,10,Fhis family before he suffered a
OL,11,F"complete aberration".
OL,13,FThe court was told the day before the
OL,14,Ffatal attack, Mohammed had gone to a
OL,15,Fmosque and started showing delusional
OL,16,Fbehaviour, including that he was
OL,17,Funclean, had seen the Prophet
OL,18,FMuhammad, was the "vessel of God" and
OL,19,Fthat the family's food was poisoned.
